<button class="accordion">What is Mental Health Law?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Mental Health Law is concerned with and governs those individuals diagnosed as suffering from mental illness, as well as those charged with their care. Mental health legislation is for an individual who cannot act legally and competently, such as those suffering from dementia, psychosis and developmental disabilities.</p>
