<button class="accordion">What decisions are not covered by the Mental Health Law?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Another person can never make some types of decisions, such as consenting to sex, marriage, divorce, adoption and voting on behalf of someone who lacks capacity, even if they are an 'Attorney' or a 'Deputy'. The Mental Capacity Act does not change this.</p>
